                    <h3 class="mtext-111 cl2 p-b-16">
                        Our Story
                    </h3>

                    <p class="stext-113 cl6 p-b-26">
                        In the heart of Chişinău, two childhood friends dreamt of blending local craftsmanship with modern style. What began in a tiny workshop above a bakery in 2015 soon blossomed into a community hub, where seamstresses, leatherworkers, and designers pooled their talents to create pieces that spoke of Moldova’s rich heritage. Each autumn, as the leaves turned gold in the city parks, our founders hosted open-air markets on Stefan cel Mare Boulevard, inviting passers-by to discover handcrafted jackets, scarves, and artisan accessories made from locally sourced wool and leather.
                    </p>

                    <p class="stext-113 cl6 p-b-26">
                        By 2018, word had spread beyond the capital: visitors from small villages and neighboring Romania began placing custom orders. Encouraged by this response, we opened our first flagship store on Pushkin Street—a bright, sunlit space lined with reclaimed wood shelves and leafy potted plants, where every garment, bag, and shoe tells a story of dedication and skill. Today, we remain true to that original vision: supporting independent artisans, investing in sustainable materials, and celebrating the creativity that pulse through Chişinău’s streets.
                    </p>

                    <p class="stext-113 cl6 p-b-26">
                        Curious to see us in action? Drop by our atelier on Ștefan cel Mare 45, chat with our master craftsmen, and watch as raw sketches become one-of-a-kind keepsakes. We’re proud to be part of Chişinău’s reviving artisan movement—and can’t wait to share the next chapter of our story with you.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

